docs.snippet: WELLINGTON, New Zealand, Dec. 28 -- One hundred and fiftynine days out of Montevideo, Uruguay, Vito Dumas, 42-yearold Argentine yachtsman and horse owner, sailed his thirtyfoot, nine-ton yacht Lehg-Lehg II single-handed into harbor here yesterday...
docs.lead_paragraph: WELLINGTON, New Zealand, Dec. 28 -- One hundred and fiftynine days out of Montevideo, Uruguay, Vito Dumas, 42-yearold Argentine yachtsman and horse owner, sailed his thirtyfoot, nine-ton yacht Lehg-Lehg II single-handed into harbor here yesterday after a lone crossing of 13,000 ocean miles separating New Zealand from South America by way of Cape Town and Tasmania.
